$$ (none of the vectors can be a linear combination of any other vector(s))</p>
<p><br />Then, by linear dependence check, $$\{\vec{v}_1,...,\vec{v}_n, \vec{v}\}$$ cannot be linearly dependent, thus making it linearly independent.<br /><br />And if this proof is valid, what might be a more mathematically notated way to show this?</p>"}], "type": "question", "tags": ["practice_week9", "student"], "tag_good": [], "unique_views": 39, "children": [{"history_size": 2, "folders": [], "data": {"embed_links": []}, "created": "2024-04-09T04:45:38Z", "bucket_order": 3, "tag_endorse": [{"role": "instructor", "name": "Shane Bauman", "endorser": {}, "admin": true, "photo": null, "id": "idt8cfyuv993c4", "photo_url": null, "us": false, "facebook_id": null}, {"role": "student", "name": "Danny Hu", "endorser": {}, "admin": false, "photo": null, "id": "lkqw8fod1ea4y5", "photo_url": null, "published": true, "us": false, "facebook_id": null}], "bucket_name": "Today", "history": [{"anon": "no", "uid": "lkqwdweou4p2j4", "subject": "", "created": "2024-04-09T04:46:44Z", "content": "I think you have the right idea but I&#39;m not sure if the proof is complete, you have argued that $$\vec{x}$$ isn&#39;t a linear combination of the other vectors, but how do you know that for instance $$\vec{v}_1$$ is still not a linear combination of the other vectors, since we now have included $$\vec{x}$$ into the other vectors? I think after showing that you can&#39;t express any $$\vec{v}_i$$ in terms of the other vectors, the proof is complete. "}, {"anon": "no", "uid": "lkqwdweou4p2j4", "subject": "", "created": "2024-04-09T04:45:38Z", "content": "I think you have the right idea but I&#39;m not sure if the proof is complete, you have argued that $$\vec{x}$$ isn&#39;t a linear combination of the other vectors, but how do you know that for instance $$\vec{v}_1$$ is still not a linear combination of the other vectors, since we now have included $$\vec{x}$$ into the other vectors?"}], "type": "s_answer", "tag_endorse_arr": ["idt8cfyuv993c4", "lkqw8fod1ea4y5"], "children": [], "id": "l